                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d646">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War, 1939/441: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Rumania</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gunther</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-09-20T20:00:00-04:00"
                            >September 20, 1939—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>137. Refer to Biddle’s 226, September 19, 9 p.m. Please take occasion orally and
                    informally to inquire of the Rumanian Government <pb facs="0699" n="691"
                        xml:id="pg_691"/> what its attitude is toward reported German demand that it
                    refuse to allow civil officials of Polish Government to leave the country, and
                    whether reports of their internment are accurate.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
